==Korean==

===Etymology===
From [[雪]] ([[snow]]) + [[濃]] (thick, strong, concentrated) + [[湯]] ([[soup]]); from the soup's whitish, cloudy appearance and concentrated flavor

===Pronunciation===
*The 2000 South Korean Revised: seol nong tang
*McCune-Reischauer: sŏl nong t'ang
*Yale: sel nong thang

===Noun===
'''[[雪]][[濃]][[湯]]''' ([[설렁탕]])

# a soup made from [[ox]] or [[beef]] bones, meat, and other seasonings

